on him at all.

517
00:22:15,595 --> 00:22:18,031
Management has me
taking shifts now.

518
00:22:18,032 --> 00:22:20,250
I need reliable guys.

519
00:22:20,251 --> 00:22:22,122
I fired Gerry last July.

520
00:22:22,123 --> 00:22:25,168
That's right when he stopped
his mortgage payments.

521
00:22:25,169 --> 00:22:26,431
He lost his house
to foreclosure

522
00:22:26,432 --> 00:22:28,563
a couple months later.

523
00:22:28,564 --> 00:22:30,565
That's the wheel
of capitalism for you.

524
00:22:30,566 --> 00:22:34,395
It'll grind you into the dust
before it stops.

525
00:22:34,396 --> 00:22:37,572
But, hey, look,
I'm sorry about Gerry.

526
00:22:37,573 --> 00:22:40,096
He seemed like a good guy,
a family man.

527
00:22:40,097 --> 00:22:41,881
When he worked here,
did the company report

528
00:22:41,882 --> 00:22:43,752
any thefts from any
of your inventory?

529
00:22:43,753 --> 00:22:45,711
We think he might have
stolen some of the explosives

530
00:22:45,712 --> 00:22:47,539
they use here, like Tovarc.

531
00:22:47,540 --> 00:22:49,541
We run inventory every week.

532
00:22:49,542 --> 00:22:51,412
Nothing has been
reported stolen--

533
00:22:51,413 --> 00:22:53,283
definitely not Tovarc.
- OK.

534
00:22:53,284 --> 00:22:54,763
Well, triple check
that inventory.

535
00:22:54,764 --> 00:22:58,027
And if you come short on
anything, even a tiny amount,

536
00:22:58,028 --> 00:22:59,856
call us right away, OK?

537
00:23:05,340 --> 00:23:06,601
I don't know
what I can tell you.

538
00:23:06,602 --> 00:23:08,777
Gerry and I have been
divorced for a year.

539
00:23:08,778 --> 00:23:11,432
Did he ever talk about
the 1985 MOVE bombing?

540
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:12,694
A little.

541
00:23:12,695 --> 00:23:14,130
I always wished
he'd open up more.

542
00:23:14,131 --> 00:23:15,436
It's what broke us up.

543
00:23:15,437 --> 00:23:18,047
Did Gerry and his family
belong to MOVE?

544
00:23:18,048 --> 00:23:20,834
Kids, wait for me.

545
00:23:23,358 --> 00:23:25,446
No, Gerry has nothing
to do with that.

546
00:23:25,447 --> 00:23:27,448
But his family lived
on that block.

547
00:23:27,449 --> 00:23:29,668
And what happened in 1985,
it destroyed them.

548
00:23:29,669 --> 00:23:31,626
Their house burned down, right?

549
00:23:31,627 --> 00:23:33,062
Yes, but it wasn't about
losing the house.

550
00:23:33,063 --> 00:23:34,803
It was about losing his home.

551
00:23:34,804 --> 00:23:37,806
Gerry's parents
never recovered.

552
00:23:37,807 --> 00:23:40,461
They had a really
ugly split-up.

553
00:23:40,462 --> 00:23:42,550
When we first met,
Gerry promised

554
00:23:42,551 --> 00:23:45,423
he'd never let that happen.

555
00:23:45,424 --> 00:23:47,642
He said we'd never,
ever get a divorce.

556
00:23:47,643 --> 00:23:51,341
We all get married thinking
it'll never happen to us.

557
00:23:51,342 --> 00:23:53,432
Until it does, right?

558
00:23:55,564 --> 00:23:56,956
I filed for divorce last year,

559
00:23:56,957 --> 00:23:59,132
but I stayed close by
for the kids.

560
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:00,307
Do you guys share custody?

561
00:24:00,308 --> 00:24:01,656
For now.

562
00:24:01,657 --> 00:24:03,658
But since he lost his job
and then the house--

563
00:24:03,659 --> 00:24:05,268
if the kids have nowhere
to stay with him,

564
00:24:05,269 --> 00:24:06,748
I might as well
move to Phoenix.

565
00:24:06,749 --> 00:24:08,402
My sister lives out there.

566
00:24:08,403 --> 00:24:10,839
It's so much cheaper.

567
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:13,886
Does Gerry know you want
custody of the kids?

568
00:24:13,887 --> 00:24:15,496
I'm not trying
to blindside him.

569
00:24:15,497 --> 00:24:17,672
I told him a few weeks ago.

570
00:24:17,673 --> 00:24:19,848
And how did he react?

571
00:24:19,849 --> 00:24:22,634
Worse than when I told him
I wanted a divorce.

572
00:24:22,635 --> 00:24:25,680
Back then, I had to hide
all the meds in our house.

573
00:24:25,681 --> 00:24:27,029
I was scared
he might do something

574
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,335
he couldn't take back.

575
00:24:28,336 --> 00:24:29,642
He already has.

576
00:24:32,427 --> 00:24:34,429
Two people are dead.

577
00:24:36,910 --> 00:24:38,433
What?

578
00:24:41,784 --> 00:24:44,090
Our kids are Gerry's world.

579
00:24:44,091 --> 00:24:45,613
And they adore him back.

580
00:24:45,614 --> 00:24:48,486
When they find out what
he's done, it'll destroy them.

581
00:24:48,487 --> 00:24:50,400
When's the last time
you spoke with him?

582
00:24:50,401 --> 00:24:52,228
A couple weeks ago.

583
00:24:52,229 --> 00:24:54,448
Gerry called me from a number
I didn't recognize.

584
00:24:54,449 --> 00:24:56,538
Let's give it a try.

585
00:25:00,281 --> 00:25:01,977
Brooklyn Men's
Emergency Shelter.

586
00:25:01,978 --> 00:25:04,937
Aditi speaking.

587
00:25:04,938 --> 00:25:07,026
Ray and Barnes are
back here on speaker.

588
00:25:07,027 --> 00:25:09,724
Gerry was eight when
they lost their family home.

589
00:25:09,725 --> 00:25:10,986
His family was involved
in a lawsuit

590
00:25:10,987 --> 00:25:12,422
against the city
of Philadelphia

591
00:25:12,423 --> 00:25:13,772
and the police department.

592
00:25:13,773 --> 00:25:15,643
Since Gerry can't provide
a stable home,

593
00:25:15,644 --> 00:25:18,080
his wife is suing him for
full custody of their kids.

594
00:25:18,081 --> 00:25:19,560
That kind of mirrors
what happened to him

595
00:25:19,561 --> 00:25:20,953
when he was little.

596
00:25:20,954 --> 00:25:23,738
Yeah, look, the police bombed
MOVE headquarters.

597
00:25:23,739 --> 00:25:25,348
Gerry loses his childhood home.

598
00:25:25,349 --> 00:25:26,785
Then he loses his family.

599
00:25:26,786 --> 00:25:29,483
So it's happening again
to him 40 years later.

600
00:25:29,484 --> 00:25:31,093
That must be
what triggered him.

601
00:25:31,094 --> 00:25:32,617
After his house was
foreclosed,

602
00:25:32,618 --> 00:25:33,792
Gerry stayed
at a men's shelter.

603
00:25:33,793 --> 00:25:35,271
We just spoke to the director.

604
00:25:35,272 --> 00:25:36,795
Yeah, you think he's going
after the shelter next?

605
00:25:36,796 --> 00:25:38,100
They've been alerted.

606
00:25:38,101 --> 00:25:39,580
Gerry even brought his
kids there and pretended

607
00:25:39,581 --> 00:25:41,103
it was a weekend excursion.

608
00:25:41,104 --> 00:25:43,453
The shelter has
a strict no-kids policy,

609
00:25:43,454 --> 00:25:44,716
so they had to ask Gerry
to leave.

610
00:25:44,717 --> 00:25:46,718
And he hasn't been back since.

611
00:25:46,719 --> 00:25:49,416
Hmm. That's harsh.

612
00:25:49,417 --> 00:25:50,460
All right.

613
00:25:50,461 --> 00:25:52,767
So no family, no home.

614
00:25:52,768 --> 00:25:54,508
This guy's got nothing to lose.

615
00:25:54,509 --> 00:25:55,944
Where's he going next?

616
00:25:55,945 --> 00:25:57,598
The shelter director
said that Gerry was friendly

617
00:25:57,599 --> 00:25:59,208
with a guy named Trent
who comes around

618
00:25:59,209 --> 00:26:01,341
for a hot meal,
but also keeps a spot

619
00:26:01,342 --> 00:26:03,212
at an encampment in Astoria.

620
00:26:03,213 --> 00:26:04,562
Sending you the cross streets.

621
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:05,911
Meet us there.

622
00:26:05,912 --> 00:26:07,870
All right.

623
00:26:10,612 --> 00:26:11,612
Oh, Hana.

624
00:26:11,613 --> 00:26:13,309
Ethan's calling you.

625
00:26:13,310 --> 00:26:14,834
Here.

626
00:26:18,446 --> 00:26:19,881
You're not going to answer it?

627
00:26:19,882 --> 00:26:20,969
Nope.

628
00:26:20,970 --> 00:26:22,623
We broke up two weeks ago.

629
00:26:22,624 --> 00:26:25,321
Oh, Hana, I'm so sorry.

630
00:26:25,322 --> 00:26:26,584
There were signs.

631
00:26:26,585 --> 00:26:28,542
I missed them.
- What kind of signs?

632
00:26:28,543 --> 00:26:29,499
I don't want
to talk about it.

633
00:26:29,500 --> 00:26:31,633
Yeah, of course.

634
00:26:34,027 --> 00:26:35,681
Have you seen this guy?

635
00:26:37,552 --> 00:26:38,987
Have you seen this man?

636
00:26:38,988 --> 00:26:40,641
OK. Thank you.

637
00:26:40,642 --> 00:26:41,816
Nobody recognizes him.

638
00:26:41,817 --> 00:26:42,904
At least that's what they say.

639
00:26:42,905 --> 00:26:44,340
Half of them won't even talk.

640
00:26:44,341 --> 00:26:45,777
They don't trust the badge.

641
00:26:45,778 --> 00:26:47,213
I mean, every major city,
cops are constantly

642
00:26:47,214 --> 00:26:48,780
harassing them,
making them move around,

643
00:26:48,781 --> 00:26:50,259
set up camps
in different places.

644
00:26:50,260 --> 00:26:51,739
That's why MOVE
didn't trust the cops--

645
00:26:51,740 --> 00:26:53,741
the constant harassment.

646
00:26:53,742 --> 00:26:55,264
It's Horus, Gerry's old boss.

647
00:26:55,265 --> 00:26:56,831
All right.

648
00:26:56,832 --> 00:26:58,441
Remy's found Trent.

649
00:26:58,442 --> 00:27:00,443
Oh, great.

650
00:27:00,444 --> 00:27:02,402
How well do you know Gerry?

651
00:27:02,403 --> 00:27:04,012
You know, about as well as

652
00:27:04,013 --> 00:27:05,753
you get to know the guy
who's stuck in the same

653
00:27:05,754 --> 00:27:07,276
sinking boat with you.

654
00:27:09,323 --> 00:27:10,715
It must be pretty hard

655
00:27:10,716 --> 00:27:12,455
to get a decent night's
sleep around here.

656
00:27:12,456 --> 00:27:13,805
Why do you stay?

657
00:27:13,806 --> 00:27:15,458
Yeah, it's just noise,
you know.

658
00:27:15,459 --> 00:27:16,634
Better than camping out
someplace

659
00:27:16,635 --> 00:27:18,331
quiet and residential.

660
00:27:18,332 --> 00:27:21,029
And you always got
the cops on your ass.

661
00:27:21,030 --> 00:27:24,032
OK, so you're here because
the neighbors don't complain.

662
00:27:24,033 --> 00:27:26,731
Out of sight, out of mind,
which is exactly

663
00:27:26,732 --> 00:27:28,863
how the public likes
their homeless, right?

664
00:27:28,864 --> 00:27:32,345
Oh, I'm sorry, the unhoused,
as though semantics

665
00:27:32,346 --> 00:27:34,826
are going to put a freaking
roof over our heads.

666
00:27:34,827 --> 00:27:37,089
Is that what you
and Gerry talked about?

667
00:27:37,090 --> 00:27:40,179
Yeah, I mean,
I'm over it, man.

668
00:27:40,180 --> 00:27:43,008
But Gerry...

669
00:27:43,009 --> 00:27:46,054
He would get all riled up.

670
00:27:46,055 --> 00:27:48,927
He talks about how
the police and politicians,

671
00:27:48,928 --> 00:27:51,799
they don't want to do their
jobs, yada, yada, you know.

672
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,148
You talking about
the housing crisis?

673
00:27:53,149 --> 00:27:55,585
I'm talking about
any crisis, man.

674
00:27:55,586 --> 00:27:56,891
Not like we elected them
to put out

675
00:27:56,892 --> 00:27:58,414
these kind of fires
or anything.

676
00:27:58,415 --> 00:28:01,287
Though, if you ask Gerry,

677
00:28:01,288 --> 00:28:03,202
he'd say they wouldn't
put out a fire

678
00:28:03,203 --> 00:28:06,466
even if that was
exactly their job.

679
00:28:06,467 --> 00:28:08,294
What do you mean by that?

680
00:28:08,295 --> 00:28:10,165
His house burned down
when he was a kid.

681
00:28:10,166 --> 00:28:12,602
He said the firefighters,
they showed up.

682
00:28:12,603 --> 00:28:14,256
They just stood around

683
00:28:14,257 --> 00:28:16,956
and watched that baby
burn to the ground.

684
00:28:19,828 --> 00:28:21,742
So that was Gerry's old boss.

685
00:28:21,743 --> 00:28:23,962
He said all of the Tovarc
is accounted for.

686
00:28:23,963 --> 00:28:26,921
However, a spool of det cord
went missing in the last day.

687
00:28:26,922 --> 00:28:29,097
They never changed the locks
after Gerry got fired,

688
00:28:29,098 --> 00:28:31,621
so he could have used
his key to steal it.

689
00:28:31,622 --> 00:28:33,232
What's det cord?

690
00:28:33,233 --> 00:28:34,668
It's a detonation cord.

691
00:28:34,669 --> 00:28:36,322
Yeah, that's uh--
it's a tiny little tube

692
00:28:36,323 --> 00:28:37,976
filled with explosives.

693
00:28:37,977 --> 00:28:39,455
We used to use that
back in Afghan

694
00:28:39,456 --> 00:28:40,761
to blow up expired ordnance.

695
00:28:40,762 --> 00:28:42,110
The arson investigator
said that Tovarc

696
00:28:42,111 --> 00:28:44,634
needs a secondary explosive
to be triggered.

697
00:28:44,635 --> 00:28:45,940
Would det cord work?

698
00:28:45,941 --> 00:28:47,942
It's exactly
what det cord's for.

699
00:28:47,943 --> 00:28:50,771
Turn a little kaboom
into a big kaboom.

700
00:28:50,772 --> 00:28:52,077
No big deal.

701
00:28:52,078 --> 00:28:53,992
That whole blast
you heard earlier--

702
00:28:53,993 --> 00:28:55,384
I mean, you got those
construction crews.

703
00:28:55,385 --> 00:28:58,737
They're running det cord
and Tovarc every damn day.

704
00:29:00,608 --> 00:29:01,956
OK.

705
00:29:01,957 --> 00:29:03,784
So Gerry could have gotten
the Tovarc from anywhere,

706
00:29:03,785 --> 00:29:05,307
including that
construction site.

707
00:29:05,308 --> 00:29:07,396
Yeah, but he didn't know
he needed the det cord

708
00:29:07,397 --> 00:29:08,789
to make it explode.

709
00:29:08,790 --> 00:29:10,486
Until he saw the first
two arsons were fires,

710
00:29:10,487 --> 00:29:11,879
not explosions.

711
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:13,489
Now that he has
these two ingredients,

712
00:29:13,490 --> 00:29:16,145
it's only a matter of time
before the big kaboom.

713
00:29:20,628 --> 00:29:21,933
Gerry told a friend that
when his house burned down,

714
00:29:21,934 --> 00:29:23,064
the fire department just
stood by and did nothing.

715
00:29:23,065 --> 00:29:24,109
Is that true?

716
00:29:24,110 --> 00:29:25,501
You don't understand.

717
00:29:25,502 --> 00:29:26,807
You're asking me
about something

718
00:29:26,808 --> 00:29:29,288
that happened 40 years ago.

719
00:29:29,289 --> 00:29:30,680
I don't remember the details.

720
00:29:30,681 --> 00:29:32,160
We're not passing judgment.

721
00:29:32,161 --> 00:29:34,597
We just need to know
what really happened.

722
00:29:34,598 --> 00:29:37,078
It was my second year
on the job.

723
00:29:37,079 --> 00:29:38,340
I was following orders.

724
00:29:38,341 --> 00:29:40,081
What were your orders?

725
00:29:40,082 --> 00:29:41,430
To stand down.

726
00:29:41,431 --> 00:29:44,085
No one expected the fire
to get so out of control.

727
00:29:44,086 --> 00:29:45,565
It got out of control

728
00:29:45,566 --> 00:29:47,959
because you didn't do
anything to stop it.

729
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:50,135
It was a mess.

730
00:29:50,136 --> 00:29:52,441
My lieutenant called it
a war zone.

731
00:29:52,442 --> 00:29:55,270
And this is the guy that
did two tours in Vietnam.

732
00:29:55,271 --> 00:29:56,837
Bullets were flying.

733
00:29:56,838 --> 00:29:58,099
Who started the shooting?

734
00:29:58,100 --> 00:29:59,622
Depends on who you ask.

735
00:29:59,623 --> 00:30:03,104
Some folks say the cops were
shooting at the MOVE folks

736
00:30:03,105 --> 00:30:04,714
trying to escape the fire.

737
00:30:04,715 --> 00:30:08,631
And the cops say
MOVE fired at them first.

738
00:30:08,632 --> 00:30:11,939
Now, what were we
supposed to do?

739
00:30:11,940 --> 00:30:15,464
We couldn't disobey
the fire commissioner.

740
00:30:15,465 --> 00:30:17,292
Is he the one
who gave the order?

741
00:30:17,293 --> 00:30:18,424
As far as I know,
he was given that order

742
00:30:18,425 --> 00:30:19,774
by the police commissioner.

743
00:30:25,388 --> 00:30:29,087
Is this why
my daughter was killed?

744
00:30:29,088 --> 00:30:32,699
Over something I did
four decades ago?

745
00:30:32,700 --> 00:30:34,048
No.

746
00:30:34,049 --> 00:30:36,356
It's over what you didn't do.

747
00:30:40,447 --> 00:30:42,317
Gerry went after a firefighter
at the scene--

748
00:30:42,318 --> 00:30:43,710
the helicopter pilot
who dropped the bomb,

749
00:30:43,711 --> 00:30:45,016
then the mayor.

750
00:30:45,017 --> 00:30:46,669
He's working his way
up the chain of command.

751
00:30:46,670 --> 00:30:48,236
Contact the fire
and police commissioners.

752
00:30:48,237 --> 00:30:49,542
We got to warn them.

753
00:30:49,543 --> 00:30:51,326
The Philadelphia police
commissioner in 1985

754
00:30:51,327 --> 00:30:52,980
was Victor Kipling.

755
00:30:52,981 --> 00:30:55,374
He lives in a senior community
in New Rochelle.

756
00:30:55,375 --> 00:30:57,202
Fire commissioner
is in New York now.

757
00:30:57,203 --> 00:30:58,638
His last known is in Brooklyn.

758
00:30:58,639 --> 00:30:59,987
You and Ray go see
the fire commissioner.

759
00:30:59,988 --> 00:31:01,423
The rest of you, with me.

760
00:31:09,302 --> 00:31:11,520
Damn incident
derailed my career.

761
00:31:11,521 --> 00:31:13,131
By incident, you mean
the bomb you ordered

762
00:31:13,132 --> 00:31:14,349
that killed 11 people?

763
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:16,221
It wasn't just any person.

764
00:31:16,222 --> 00:31:19,354
They were disrupting the city
and endangering the police.

765
00:31:19,355 --> 00:31:20,573
What about the five kids?

766
00:31:20,574 --> 00:31:23,010
How were they
endangering the police?

767
00:31:23,011 --> 00:31:25,926
I mean, those five kids weren't
the only collateral damage.

768
00:31:25,927 --> 00:31:29,016
200 homes burnt that day.

769
00:31:29,017 --> 00:31:30,017
This is Gerry Colworth.

770
00:31:30,018 --> 00:31:31,279
He lost his childhood home.

771
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:32,759
Do you recognize him?

772
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:34,369
No.

773
00:31:34,370 --> 00:31:36,589
But I do remember
the Colworth name.

774
00:31:36,590 --> 00:31:38,373
His parents were part
of a lawsuit against the city

